\f0\b\fs32 \cf0 15. Implementation Roadmap
\fs48 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa106\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf0 15.1 Phase I \'96 Silent Foundations
\fs36 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0\fs32 \cf0 The first implementation phase establishes the substrate upon which all higher-order capability depends. Its work is primarily infrastructural: quietly ingesting the organisation\'92s existing intellectual capital, structuring it into formal logic, mapping dependencies, and enforcing role-conditioned access. This is not a public deployment stage. It is a foundational build-out, executed with discretion, enabling future transparency and operational integration once the logic bedrock has been set.
\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf0 1. Ingestion of Institutional Artefacts\uc0\u8232 
\f2\b0 The platform absorbs the organisation\'92s implicit and explicit knowledge inventory. Policies, SOPs, planning files, technical reports, risk memoranda, underwriting models, design specifications, emails, precedent decisions, dispute outcomes, and internal committee notes are parsed and indexed. Transcripts from workshops, approval chains, onboarding procedures, legal interpretations, and compliance reviews are extracted into structured insight. No reasoning is lost to obscurity or personnel attrition. The initial objective is comprehensiveness \'97 assembling the clearest possible picture of what the institution 
\f1\i believes
\f2\i0  and how it has historically reasoned.
\fs24 \

\f0\b\fs32 2. Structural Conversion of Knowledge\uc0\u8232 
\f2\b0 Narrative text is lifted into formalised logic objects. Claims are shaped into rule statements with scope boundaries, evidence references, applicability conditions, and review cycles. Ratios, thresholds, procedural sequences, and risk triggers are expressed as executable structures. Precedent decisions are converted into contextual entities that reveal the logic applied, evidence relied upon, interpretation adopted, and authority level involved. The platform begins to transform institutional memory into structured doctrine.
\fs24 \

\f0\b\fs32 3. Mapping Dependencies and Logical Architecture\uc0\u8232 
\f2\b0 Key nodes are interconnected into the knowledge graph. Planning stipulations propagate into procedural requirements; underwriting ratios connect to covenant formulations; regulatory clauses link to compliance triggers and audit conditions. The web of institutional reasoning comes into view: contradictions surface, ambiguity pockets are exposed, high-centrality nodes are identified, and the latent architecture of organisational doctrine becomes inspectable. Observability is established at conceptual level, even before operational integration.
\fs24 \

\f0\b\fs32 4. Role-Conditioned Logic Framework\uc0\u8232 
\f2\b0 Access and retrieval are bound to organisational mandate. Policies with legal or commercial sensitivity are restricted to authorised tiers. Exception logic, discretionary pathways, and negotiation precedents are made visible only to senior roles. Procedural tasks, compliance steps, and threshold rules are exposed to operational staff in filtered, contextualised form. The platform establishes alignment between institutional authority and logic visibility, ensuring that no user interacts with knowledge outside their mandate. This preserves governance integrity before any automated reasoning is deployed.
\fs24 \

\f0\b\fs32 5. Early Provenance Tracking and Version Hygiene\uc0\u8232 
\f2\b0 From inception, knowledge entities carry authorship, timestamps, evidence references, and lineage notes. Even at this silent stage, logic can be defended: it is already tethered to source material and contextual justification. Nodes are versioned rather than overwritten, preserving institutional evolution. The platform begins as it intends to continue: treating knowledge not as text but as accountable doctrine.
\fs24 \

\f0\b\fs32 6. Internal Knowledge Council Formation\uc0\u8232 
\f2\b0 Councils (or equivalent stewardship bodies) are constituted to review extracted logic, approve authoritative nodes, resolve contradictions, and validate evidence sufficiency. Their scrutiny ensures that what is ingested does not become doctrine merely because it is inherited. Phase I relies on these custodians to refine and sanction the emerging knowledge graph.
\fs24 \

\f0\b\fs32 7. Zero-Noise Deployment\uc0\u8232 
\f2\b0 Public-facing features remain dormant. Staff continue normal operations with minimal disruption, while the platform quietly constructs institutional clarity behind the scenes. No premature workflow gating or UI overlays interfere with existing rhythm. Phase I is infrastructural archaeology \'97 uncovering, interpreting, and structuring organisational knowledge with precision.
\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf0 In this foundational phase, the institution does not yet 
\f1\i use
\f2\i0  InternalWiki.com to execute decisions at scale. Instead, it prepares for a future where reasoning is traceable, logic is provable, and operational conduct is governed by structured doctrine. By moving slowly and silently, Phase I ensures that future automation rests on an epistemically sound base rather than inherited assumptions or incomplete documentation.
\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa106\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf0 15.2 Phase II \'96 Active Query Layer
\fs36 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0\fs32 \cf0 With the foundational substrate structured, mapped, and governed, Phase II activates the first functional surface of InternalWiki.com: an organisational query layer that returns structured reasoning rather than unstructured narrative. This phase marks the point where institutional knowledge becomes interrogable, explainable, and practically usable, but still short of workflow enforcement or automation. The institution learns to 
\f1\i talk to itself
\f2\i0  through the logic it now owns.
\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf0 1. Natural-Language Interrogation of Institutional Doctrine\uc0\u8232 
\f2\b0 Staff query the platform in everyday language:\uc0\u8232 How do we treat this regulatory condition?\u8232 What evidence is needed for approval?\u8232 Which thresholds govern this risk class?\u8232 What are the jurisdiction constraints for this procedural step?
\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf0 Rather than returning prose, the system responds with structured institutional logic: decision rules, compliance triggers, procedural sequencing, authority tiers, evidence references, precedent nodes, and fallback conditions. Knowledge becomes an interpretable substrate, not a document archive.
