\f0\b \cf0 5. Versioning and Historical Storage\uc0\u8232 
\f2\b0 Outdated or biased logic is not erased. It is archived with lineage and evidence notes, enabling future auditors, investigators, or internal reviewers to understand the historical context that gave rise to the bias and the steps taken to correct it. This protects institutional integrity and prevents historical revisionism.
\fs24 \

\f0\b\fs32 6. Interpretive Diversity Through Council Design\uc0\u8232 
\f2\b0 Knowledge Councils incorporate cross-disciplinary expertise and regulatory exposure. Incorporating legal, operational, compliance, risk, and contextual stakeholders reduces epistemic monoculture. Divergent viewpoints challenge inherited assumptions and reveal blind spots. Bias becomes harder to sustain when doctrinal review is distributed among qualified stewards rather than confined to legacy power centres.
\fs24 \

\f0\b\fs32 7. Recertification and Expiry Cycles\uc0\u8232 
\f2\b0 Expiry mechanisms prevent outdated or previously justified logic from surviving indefinitely. Policy assumptions that were once evidence-backed may no longer reflect current legal, social, or operational conditions. Recertification cycles force fresh validation, ensuring that bias embedded in historic data or precedent does not ossify into unchallenged doctrine.
\fs24 \

\f0\b\fs32 8. Detection Through Execution Data\uc0\u8232 
\f2\b0 Phase III and IV execution data reveal whether certain groups or categories are systematically affected by logic. Repeated exception requests, persistent friction patterns, or disproportionate rejections trigger review. The institution can interrogate not only the doctrine, but its consequences \'97 grounding correction in lived evidence rather than inference.
\fs24 \

\f0\b\fs32 9. Explicit Prohibition on Silent Overrides\uc0\u8232 
\f2\b0 Where logic is circumvented informally \'97 a classic indicator of institutional bias \'97 the platform detects bypass behaviour and forces escalation. If exceptions are routinely applied to specific cases or groups, councils must interrogate whether the logic is unjust, outdated, or inaccurate. Shadow practices cannot coexist silently with structured doctrine.
\fs24 \

\f0\b\fs32 10. Cultural Normalisation of Challenge\uc0\u8232 
\f2\b0 Finally, InternalWiki.com shifts cultural expectation. Because all logic is inspectable, evidence-linked, and intellectually traceable, challenge is natural rather than confrontational. Staff engage doctrine as an analytical object, not personal legacy. Bias becomes a correctable logic flaw, not a taboo accusation.
\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf0 By formalising mechanisms for surfacing, interrogating, and rectifying institutional bias, the platform ensures that knowledge is not treated as unexamined inheritance but as accountable doctrine. Bias is not defeated by goodwill; it is engineered out through structure, evidence standards, and transparent governance pathways.
